Moving from philosophy, sciences and everyday life to information retrieval, we find a very vague situation. Users of search engines are ‘dictated’ to provide a very concise and specific query that is extremely efficient for focalized search (e.g., looking for a specific hotel). On the other hand, studies show that \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
